WEBVTT

00:04.030 --> 00:06.763
This is outrageous, sir.

00:06.764 --> 00:09.922
Y-you are nothing but a
well-dressed loan shark.

00:09.923 --> 00:11.635
Ms. Rodgers, I assure you,

00:11.636 --> 00:13.912
this is a very competitive interest rate...

00:14.543 --> 00:16.488
...considering your financial history.

00:16.489 --> 00:18.156
However, if your son cosigns--

00:18.157 --> 00:19.362
- Yes.
- No, no, no, no.

00:19.363 --> 00:20.672
This is my loan, not his,

00:20.673 --> 00:23.473
to pay for repairs to my
acting studio, not his.

00:23.474 --> 00:25.740
If you just let me cosign the loan,

00:25.741 --> 00:27.083
or I could just give you the money.

00:27.084 --> 00:29.520
Richard, I'm a businesswoman now.

00:29.521 --> 00:31.549
I do not want your money.
I do not want your signature.

00:31.550 --> 00:32.439
Thank you very much.

00:32.441 --> 00:33.713
It's the principle.

00:33.714 --> 00:35.004
No, Ms. Rodgers,

00:35.005 --> 00:36.424
it's the interest.

00:36.425 --> 00:39.070
And I've just lost mine. Excuse me.

00:40.056 --> 00:42.446
I have $1 million...

00:42.447 --> 00:45.025
Into this now, so...

00:47.956 --> 00:49.373
What do you want, Castle?

00:49.374 --> 00:51.038
Tell me you need me.

00:51.809 --> 00:52.925
Excuse me?

00:52.926 --> 00:54.092
I'm stuck at a bank,

00:54.093 --> 00:56.633
helping my mother get a
loan from my banker.

00:56.634 --> 00:58.300
Please tell me that there's
a murder somewhere

00:58.301 --> 00:59.548
we could be solving.

00:59.549 --> 01:00.220
Uh, sorry,

01:00.221 --> 01:01.923
there is no dead body,
just a lot of paperwork,

01:01.924 --> 01:04.655
which welcome you to come
and do your share for once.

01:04.656 --> 01:06.174
I wonder if it's worse being here or

01:06.175 --> 01:07.606
being there doing paperwork.

01:07.607 --> 01:09.864
You know how can we be partners
when I'm chasing down bad guys,

01:09.865 --> 01:12.622
and as soon as there are paperwork,
I'm on an solo mission?

01:14.331 --> 01:15.382
What?

01:22.315 --> 01:26.218
I think this bank is about to be robbed.

01:26.664 --> 01:28.603
Really? Are you that bored?

01:31.577 --> 01:34.362
There's a man and a woman here

01:34.683 --> 01:36.512
dressed in scrubs,

01:36.890 --> 01:40.758
and both of them have suspicious
bulges in their jackets.

01:41.599 --> 01:43.093
Castle, I think your writer's imagination

01:43.094 --> 01:44.870
is getting away with you.

01:47.157 --> 01:49.160
Everybody, get down on the floor!

01:49.161 --> 01:51.233
It's not my imagination.

01:51.234 --> 01:53.337
It's definitely not my imagination.

01:54.954 --> 01:56.404
Move, move, move, move,
move, move, move, move.

01:56.405 --> 01:58.794
Oh my God!

01:58.795 --> 01:59.817
Castle, what's happening?

01:59.818 --> 02:00.952
Oh, my God.

02:00.953 --> 02:02.649
On the floor! Get down! Move, move.

02:02.650 --> 02:03.443
Ok, ok.

02:05.489 --> 02:06.384
Where are you?

02:06.385 --> 02:08.554
I'm at the New Amsterdam
Bank & Trust on Lex.

02:08.555 --> 02:10.066
Esposito, there's a 10-30,

02:10.067 --> 02:11.909
New Amsterdam Bank & Trust on Lex.

02:11.910 --> 02:12.967
Call dispatch.

02:12.968 --> 02:15.591
10-30? Since when we are
handling bank-robbery cause?

02:15.592 --> 02:16.994
Castle's there.

02:17.620 --> 02:19.112
Slide up your cell phones. Now!

02:19.113 --> 02:22.054
- Cell phones.
- Hurry up, now, come on!

02:22.286 --> 02:24.823
Yo, you get that one? Slide that up here.

02:24.988 --> 02:26.603
I said slide up your mobiles!

02:26.604 --> 02:29.909
- Move away from your stations.
- Slide 'em up. Come on.

02:29.944 --> 02:32.746
I'm hiding behind a desk with my mother,

02:32.911 --> 02:34.606
but I can see everything.

02:35.827 --> 02:36.961
They're wearing doctor scrubs.

02:36.962 --> 02:39.100
One of them is emptying the cash drawers.

02:39.507 --> 02:41.392
You, bank manager... move over here.

02:41.393 --> 02:44.082
Another one is going for the bank manager.

02:45.637 --> 02:47.425
He's getting manager's key.

02:48.863 --> 02:50.740
He's going to the back of bank.

02:52.522 --> 02:54.091
We got squad cars en route.

02:54.092 --> 02:55.516
Castle, I need you to
listen very carefully.

02:55.517 --> 02:56.672
How many are there?

02:56.673 --> 02:59.923
There are three.

03:02.497 --> 03:04.062
Make that four.

03:04.193 --> 03:06.871
So you're the hero I'm
gonna make an example of.

03:09.025 --> 03:10.605
Sorry. Your friend can't talk right now.

03:10.606 --> 03:13.145
I wouldn't worry about him.
I'd worry about yourself.

03:13.146 --> 03:14.924
I've got squad cars on their way.

03:14.925 --> 03:15.654
Are you a cop?

03:15.655 --> 03:16.567
You called a cop?

03:16.568 --> 03:19.775
No. We were already on line
when you guys came in.

03:19.776 --> 03:21.931
Listen to me. So far, nobody has been hurt

03:21.932 --> 03:23.670
and nothing has been stolen.

03:23.671 --> 03:26.598
So if you just leave the
same way that you came in,

03:26.599 --> 03:28.170
you can just disappear.

03:28.225 --> 03:30.355
You gonna promise not to come look for me?

03:30.922 --> 03:33.425
I don't look. I hunt.

03:33.426 --> 03:35.895
And trust me, you don't want that.

03:36.261 --> 03:37.339
So leave now,

03:37.340 --> 03:39.446
and this will just be a
quirky little article

03:39.447 --> 03:41.570
in the Metro section.

03:43.931 --> 03:45.104
Sorry, sweetheart.

03:45.105 --> 03:47.088
I'd rather make the front page.

03:48.776 --> 03:49.981
Let's go.

03:50.124 --> 03:51.546
Dr. Howser, Dr. Quinn,

03:51.547 --> 03:53.191
cops are gonna be here
sooner than we thought.

03:53.192 --> 03:54.872
Now kiss the floor, like the others.

03:54.873 --> 03:56.854
Come on. You, too. Get down.

03:57.018 --> 03:58.528
Dr. Huxtable, let's go.

03:58.529 --> 03:59.779
Bank cameras are down.

03:59.780 --> 04:01.621
Memory drives are destroyed.

04:05.275 --> 04:06.435
Cops!

04:06.436 --> 04:08.901
All right, doctors, we trained for this.

04:08.902 --> 04:10.299
You know what to do.

04:10.300 --> 04:13.263
Looks like we're all gonna get
to know each other a lot better.

